string2Date

private static java.util.Date string2Date(java.lang.String date)
YYMMDDhhmm where:
  • YY = last two digits of the year (00-99)
  • MM = month (01-12)
  • DD = day (01-31)
  • hh = hour (00-23)
  • mm = minute (00-59)
Java format is (yyMMddHHmm).

Parameters:
date - in String format.
Returns:
Throws:
java.lang.NumberFormatException - if there is contains non number on date parameter.
java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the date length in String format is less than 10.
